# CRM Demo Workflow Rule

## Scope
- Main app lives in `crm_monuments (1).html`.
- Keep delivery as a single file unless user explicitly asks otherwise.

## Change Discipline
- Prefer minimal, targeted edits over broad refactors.
- Preserve behavior unless user asks for behavior changes.
- Keep backward compatibility for existing `PT` entries and template data.
- When changing constructor/template logic, update both flows if they share helpers.

## UI Safety
- Keep controls usable in narrow columns (`select` arrow area, truncation, spacing).
- Do not remove existing actions; compact UI is allowed if discoverability remains.
- For icon-only actions, include `title` and `aria-label`.

## Communication Style (UA)
- Default replies in Ukrainian.
- Keep answers concise and practical; avoid long theory unless requested.
- For changes: state what changed, where, and expected visible effect.
- Prioritize UI/UX outcomes and quick verification steps.

## Validation
- After substantive edits, run lints on edited files.
- Mention required hard refresh (`Ctrl+F5`) when CSS/JS cache may mask changes.

